    "recap_headline": "Texas A&M",
    "recap_text": "BRYAN-COLLEGE STATION\u00a0\u2013\nNo. 23 Texas A&M dropped the middle game of the series with No. 7 Georgia, 8-2, Saturday afternoon from Olsen Field at Blue Bell Park.\nThe Bulldogs (20-4, 4-1) drilled six home runs in the contest to power past the Aggies (17-5, 1-4). Jordy Oriach opened the scoring with a solo shot to right field in the second inning. Georgia extended its lead to 3-0 in the top of the third behind back-to-back homers from Tre Phelps and Daniel Jackson.\nTexas A&M responded in the bottom half of the frame with a\nCaden Sorrell\nRBI double, cutting the Bulldogs' edge to two runs.\nKolby Branch got the run back for Georgia in the fourth inning with a solo shot to left-center field.\nIn the bottom of the fifth, the Maroon & White made it a two-run ballgame on an RBI groundout from\nChris Hacopian\n.\nThe Bulldogs pushed across four runs in the top of the sixth behind a pair of homers and an RBI single, sealing the final score at 8-2.\nWeston Moss\n(3-2) suffered his second loss of the season after allowing four earned runs on five hits in 3.1 innings pitched. The righty punched out four batters and issued one walk.\nGavin Lyons\nrelieved Moss in the fourth inning, conceding three runs on four hits in 2.0 innings pitched.\nHunter Vincent\nentered next but could only record one out before allowing one run and two walks. The Aggies' most effective reliever was\nGrant Cunningham\n, who worked the final 3.1 innings in scoreless fashion, striking out two.\nTOP PLAYERS\nCaden Sorrell\n\u2013 2-for-5, 1 RBI, 2 2B\nGrant Cunningham\n\u2013 3.1 IP, 1 H, 0 R, 1 BB, 2 K\nSCORING SUMMARY\nT2 | Oriach knocked a solo shot to put Georgia on the board first. A&M 0, UGA 1.\nT3 | The Bulldogs tacked on two more runs with back-to-back homers from Phelps and Jackson. A&M 0, UGA 3.\nB3 |\nBoston Kellner\nwas hit by a pitch and scored on a Sorrell double to right-center field. A&M 1, UGA 3.\nT4| Branch blasted a solo homer to left-center field. A&M 1, UGA 4.\nB5 |\nGavin Grahovac\nled off with a double down the left field line and advanced to third on a Sorrell groundout. Hacopian plated the run with a high groundout to the second baseman. A&M 2, UGA 4.\nT6 | Oriach singled up the middle and Branch drove a home run to left field. With one out, Ryan Black knocked a solo shot to right-center. Jackson and Michael O'Shaughnessy walked with two outs. Henry Allen plated a run on a single to left field. A&M 2, UGA 8.\nGAME NOTES\nSaturday's contest marked the 28th meeting all-time between the clubs. Despite the loss, the Aggies still lead the series 16-12.\nBlue Bell Park held 6,925 fans for Saturday's middle game.\nTerrence Kiel II\nand Kellner have reached base safely in all 22 games.\nGrahovac and Sorrell increased their respective on-base streaks to 16 games.\nJake Duer\nand Sorrell upped their team-best multi-hit game total to 11.\nCunningham tossed a season-high 3.1 innings.\nUP NEXT\nTexas A&M and Georgia wrap up the series Sunday, March 22, with first pitch slated for 3 p.m. from Olsen Field at Blue Bell Park. Sunday's finale will broadcast nationally on SEC Network, and fans can follow along on the radio at 1150 AM/93.7 FM The Zone.\nFollow the Aggies\nVisit for more information on Texas A&M baseball. Fans can keep up to date with the A&M baseball team on\u00a0Facebook, Instagram\u00a0and X by following @aggiebaseball.",
